author: Pixel Crushers
description: This project demonstrates the major features of the Dialogue System for Unity.  In this sci-fi scene, the player's squad has been sent to intercept launch codes to stop the launch of a weapon against their homeworld.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Private Hart offers the quest to hack the emperor's computer to get the launch codes.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Sergeant Graves offers the quest to hold back enemy forces.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: The computer interface through which the player can get the launch codes.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: The evil emperor's guards. They have a note with the terminal password.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: This actor is used for enemies to bark (one-off gameplay lines).

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Your squad has infiltrated the evil Emperor's weapons factory to intercept launch codes to stop the mega-weapon aimed at your homeworld.

fields.title: Success Description
fields.value: You get the launch codes and can redirect the weapon away from your homeworld.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Sergeant Graves wants you to halt the enemy advance by taking out five of them.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Show alert messages during gameplay by setting this variable.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Tracks the number of enemies killed.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Tracks whether the player has found the launch codes.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Holds player's input from Terminal conversation's TextInput() command.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: This conversation occurs between the Player and Private Hart, who explains the main quest (Get the Launch Codes). Nodes' Conditions fields branch the conversation based on the current quest state.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: Used if the quest is unassigned. Cuts to an immediate closeup of the speaker (Hart).

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: We need to intercept the launch codes before the enemy launches their weapon at our home world.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Any luck downloading the launch codes?

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: You got the codes! Now we can get out of here. (End of demo)

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: I can't break into the computer. It's password protected.

dialogueEntries.userScript:
SetQuestState("Get the Launch Codes", "active");
Variable["Alert"] = "Mission: Get the Launch Codes"

fields.title: Description
fields.value: This quest runs the Enemy Attack quest.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: There's [lua(5 - Variable["enemiesKilled"])] left. We can do it.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Help me take out those enemies before they call for reinforcements!

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: Great job taking out those enemies!

fields.title: Description
fields.value: This conversation demonstrates how to use the dialogue system for other kinds of interaction (searching a body). The first node moves the camera to the "Down" angle on the body over 1 second. The last node moves back to the original position.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: This was one of the evil emperor's guards.

fields.title: Dialogue Text
fields.value: He has a note that reads: password is 'dominate'.

fields.title: Description
fields.value: This conversation is for the computer terminal where the player can download the launch codes to complete the Get the Launch Codes quest. It overrides the Default Sequence to delay instead of playing voiceover (see below).

fields.title: Sequence
fields.value:
Camera(Terminal Camera Angle,,1);
TextInput(Text Field UI,Password,password)

dialogueEntries.userScript:
SetQuestState("Get the Launch Codes", "success");
Variable["Alert"] = "Mission Complete: Launch Codes Acquired"
